    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of your tender of resignation dated March 7 and of your dispatch 94 of
                    April 4, I am directed by the President to inform you that your resignation is
                    accepted. You are therefore authorized to quit your post at your early
                    convenience, leaving the archives and property of the legation in custody of
                    Consul-General Severance without diplomatic functions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
